In this conference call, President Obama discusses his nomination of Chief Judge Merrick Garland for the Supreme Court. He emphasizes Garland's qualifications and bipartisan support, and argues that the Senate should give him a timely hearing and an up or down vote. Obama also asserts that the American people have already had a say in the matter through the 2012 election, and that the Supreme Court needs an additional justice to address important issues. He calls for the American people to make their voices heard and urge senators to act fairly. Obama concludes by emphasizing the importance of the integrity of the government system and expresses his commitment to fighting for his nomination during the remainder of his term.